ABUJA – Nigeria on Thursday reported an astronomical increase in the number of coronavirus cases. At 381 new COVID-19 cases, the country recorded its highest  daily infections since the index case in February.The new cases took Nigeria’s total to 3,526.According to the update by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) released late on Thursday, Lagos, which has remained the epicentre, had 183 new cases, followed by Kano and Jigawa with 55 and 44 new infections respectively. There was no fresh case reported in the Federal Capital Territory,  Abuja. The full detail reads: 381 new cases of #COVID19; 183-Lagos55-Kano44-Jigawa19-Zamfara19-Bauchi11-Katsina9-Borno8-Kwara7-Kaduna6-Gombe5-Ogun4-Sokoto3-Oyo3-Rivers2-Niger1-Akwa Ibom1-Enugu1-Plateau 3526 cases of #COVID19 in NigeriaDischarged: 601Deaths: 107 ABUJA - Lagos State, the Federal Capital Territory, Kano and Oyo have spiked the number Nigeria's confirmed Coronavirus cases with the addition of 35 confirmed infections as at late Thursday night.Lagos State has 19 new infections with FCT contributing nine. Kano and Oyo have five and two new cases respectively… April 16, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - Lagos, the epicentre of coronavirus in Nigeria and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) on Saturday got observers worried as both cities recorded new infections in huge numbers.According to the report by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), there were 220 new cases out of which Lagos and… May 3, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - The COVID-19 situation in Kano State took a dangerous dimension on Friday as the state for the second day topped Lagos, the epicentre of the pandemic in Nigeria. Out of the 238 new cases announced by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), Kano recorded 92 new cases… May 1, 2020 In "Top Stories"